=head1 DESCRIPTION

The drift summary of the enabled control.

Amazon Web Services Control Tower expects the enabled control
configuration to include all supported and governed Regions. If the
enabled control differs from the expected configuration, it is defined
to be in a state of drift. You can repair this drift by resetting the
enabled control.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 DriftStatus => Str

The drift status of the enabled control.

Valid values:

=over

=item *

C<DRIFTED>: The C<enabledControl> deployed in this configuration
doesnE<rsquo>t match the configuration that Amazon Web Services Control
Tower expected.

=item *

C<IN_SYNC>: The C<enabledControl> deployed in this configuration
matches the configuration that Amazon Web Services Control Tower
expected.

=item *

C<NOT_CHECKING>: Amazon Web Services Control Tower does not check drift
for this enabled control. Drift is not supported for the control type.

=item *

C<UNKNOWN>: Amazon Web Services Control Tower is not able to check the
drift status for the enabled control.

=back




